==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: somnolism
<hw>som"no*lism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
somnolent state induced by animal magnetism (hypnotism); the hypnotic
state.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Thomas (Med.
Dict.).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the act or process of inducing the hypnotic state;
hypnotism; hyonotizing.</def> <au>Stedman.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somnopathy</ent>⟦br⟧
